To fix the error "The method setRestTemplate(RestTemplate) is undefined for the type FlinkApiController", you should modify the FlinkApiController class to add a setter method for the RestTemplate class.

You can modify the FlinkApiController class as follows:

```java
import org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate;

public class FlinkApiController {
    private RestTemplate restTemplate;

    public void setRestTemplate(RestTemplate restTemplate) {
        this.restTemplate = restTemplate;
    }

    // ... other methods
}
```

Now the setter method `setRestTemplate` is available for the FlinkApiController class and you can use it in the test case.

